-- Red Sox’s World Series Clincher Draws 18% Ratings Boost on Fox
-- B y   E b e n   N o v y - W i l l i a m s   a n d   M a s o n   L e v i n s o n
-- 2013-10-31T14:00:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-10-31/red-sox-s-world-series-clincher-draws-18-ratings-boost-on-fox.html
The World Series-clinching victory
by the  Boston Red Sox  last night drew television ratings in
major markets that were 18 percent higher than the final game a
year ago.  The Red Sox’s 6-1 win over the St. Louis Cardinals in Game
6 of Major League Baseball’s championship series attracted 12.5
percernt of viewers in the 56 biggest U.S. media markets,
according to figures provided by News Corp.’s Fox network, which
broadcast the game.  The final game in 2012, a victory by the  San Francisco
Giants  over the Detroit Tigers, drew a 10.6 big-city rating as
it completed a four-game sweep, Fox said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Larry Siddons at 
 lsiddons@bloomberg.net  